						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Rājakēsarivarman [Gaṇḍarāditya], 6th year = A.D. 955.</p>						

						<p>Sale of land to Vēdivēḷān by the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Śrīkaṇṭha-chaturvēdimaṅgalam for the purpose of making the temple streets <hi rend="italic">(maḍaviḷāgam)</hi> of the Tiruveṟumbiyūr-āḻvār temple. A piece of land given to the <hi rend="italic">tiruppadiyam</hi> reciters is mentioned among the boundaries.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, Vol. XIII, No. 140.)</p>						

